                            <comment id="14471634" author="tim_yates" created="Wed, 3 Aug 2011 03:37:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the patch needs to go into &lt;tt&gt;org/codehaus/groovy/runtime/ConvertedMap.java&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This catches the &lt;tt&gt;toString()&lt;/tt&gt; instance, but there must be a nicer way of catching all of the base methods of &lt;tt&gt;Object&lt;/tt&gt; (if they don&apos;t exist as closures in the Map itself)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-none&quot;&gt;Index: src/main/org/codehaus/groovy/runtime/ConvertedMap.java
===================================================================
--- src/main/org/codehaus/groovy/runtime/ConvertedMap.java	(revision 22732)
+++ src/main/org/codehaus/groovy/runtime/ConvertedMap.java	(working copy)
@@ -42,6 +42,9 @@
             throws Throwable {
         Map m = (Map) getDelegate();
         Closure cl = (Closure) m.get(method.getName());
+        if( cl == null &amp;amp;&amp;amp; &quot;toString&quot;.equals(method.getName() ) ) {
+            return m.toString() ;
+        }
         if (cl == null) {
             throw new UnsupportedOperationException();
         }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14471469" author="tim_yates" created="Wed, 3 Aug 2011 03:51:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached Test case which goes in &lt;tt&gt;src/test/groovy/bugs&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14471649" author="trygvea" created="Sun, 11 Sep 2011 13:17:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I suggest this is a blocker - it makes familiar constructs like &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;[run: {}] as &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Runnable&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;fail.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14471879" author="tim_yates" created="Fri, 23 Sep 2011 10:02:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added a test for the Runnable failing example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-none&quot;&gt;diff --git a/src/test/groovy/bugs/Groovy4857Bug.groovy b/src/test/groovy/bugs/Groovy4857Bug.groovy
index 3b20426..b6f8a62 100644
--- a/src/test/groovy/bugs/Groovy4857Bug.groovy
+++ b/src/test/groovy/bugs/Groovy4857Bug.groovy
@@ -38,5 +38,12 @@ class Groovy4857Bug extends GroovyTestCase {
             assert e.class.name == &apos;groovy.lang.MissingMethodException&apos;
         }
     }
+
+    void testTrygveAmundsensExample() {
+        def val = new GroovyShell().evaluate &quot;&quot;&quot;
+            [run: {}] as Runnable
+        &quot;&quot;&quot;
+        assert val instanceof Runnable
+    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Which works now on trunk (or should that be &apos;master&apos; now we&apos;re using git?) &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
